snippet.textDisplay:
The Thanos mask was not good. Facial expressions and mouth-movements are important to conveying the menace and capacity of the Mad Titan. Perhaps a skilfully applied makeup and light prosthetic that allow more acting expression might have done better. Voice and delivery for the Thanos, was excellent However, there is so much more good about this!
Great disses, great track from Epistra, great lines, lots of classical comic and historical references, and special congratulations to Nice Peter for his portrayal of Oppenheimer. "What have I done? What am I going to do?" This is really inspiring for a character of a troubled hero, or a sympathetic villain in fear of what they have created, and might be called to do again.
snippet.textOriginal:
The Thanos mask was not good.  Facial expressions and mouth-movements are important to conveying the menace and capacity of the Mad Titan.  Perhaps a skilfully applied makeup and light prosthetic that allow more acting expression might have done better.  Voice and delivery for the Thanos, was excellent  However, there is so much more  good about this!
Great disses, great track from Epistra, great lines, lots of classical comic and historical references, and special congratulations to Nice Peter for his portrayal of Oppenheimer.  "What have I done?  What am I going to do?"  This is really inspiring for a character of a troubled hero, or a sympathetic villain in fear of what they have created, and might be called to do again.
